{"id":856,"date":"2020-11-01T20:16:50","date_gmt":"2020-11-01T20:16:50","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.sleepiest.com\/?p=856"},"modified":"2020-11-01T20:16:51","modified_gmt":"2020-11-01T20:16:51","slug":"why-hitting-snooze-could-be-bad-for-your-health","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.sleepiest.com\/blog\/why-hitting-snooze-could-be-bad-for-your-health\/","title":{"rendered":"Why Hitting &#8220;Snooze&#8221; Could Be Bad For Your Health"},"content":{"rendered":"<div class=\"st-post-container gutenberg-block\">\n<p>We&#8217;re all guilty of hitting &#8216;snooze&#8217; on our alarms each morning we wake up.<\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"st-post-container gutenberg-block\">\n\n<\/div><div class=\"st-post-container gutenberg-block\">\n<p>While some people are great in the morning and can easily hop out of bed, ready to attack the day, the rest of us struggle to drag ourselves out from under our comfy duvets. We tell ourselves that &#8216;just a couple more minutes&#8217; in bed will make us feel better.<\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"st-post-container gutenberg-block\">\n\n<\/div><div class=\"st-post-container gutenberg-block\">\n<p>Well, quite unsurprisingly, it doesn&#8217;t. According to experts, hitting the snooze button could be causing you to feel even more tired.<\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"st-post-container gutenberg-block\">\n\n<\/div><div class=\"st-post-container gutenberg-block\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"682\" src=\"https:\/\/www.sleepiest.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/hit-snooze.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-857\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.sleepiest.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/hit-snooze.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/www.sleepiest.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/hit-snooze-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/www.sleepiest.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/hit-snooze-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n<\/div><div class=\"st-post-container gutenberg-block\">\n\n<\/div><div class=\"st-post-container gutenberg-block\">\n<p>This is because giving yourself an extra 5 or 10 minutes of sleep doesn&#8217;t allow your body to fall back into a deep slumber. You interrupt your brain in the middle of a sleep cycle.<\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"st-post-container gutenberg-block\">\n\n<\/div><div class=\"st-post-container gutenberg-block\">\n<p>If you have had a good night&#8217;s sleep and you allow yourself to gently wake up, rather than fall straight back asleep, then the snooze button could benefit your waking up the process. However, generally, people who hit the snooze button fall straight back asleep, which results in fragmented sleep.<\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"st-post-container gutenberg-block\">\n\n<\/div><div class=\"st-post-container gutenberg-block\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"682\" src=\"https:\/\/www.sleepiest.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/snooze-cat.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-858\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.sleepiest.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/snooze-cat.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/www.sleepiest.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/snooze-cat-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/www.sleepiest.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/snooze-cat-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n<\/div><div class=\"st-post-container gutenberg-block\">\n\n<\/div><div class=\"st-post-container gutenberg-block\">\n<h2>But does hitting snooze actually help or hinder you?<\/h2>\n<\/div><div class=\"st-post-container gutenberg-block\">\n\n<\/div><div class=\"st-post-container gutenberg-block\">\n<p>Hitting snooze regularly can also cause an association in your brain between hearing your alarm and having a delayed reaction to waking up.<\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"st-post-container gutenberg-block\">\n\n<\/div><div class=\"st-post-quote gutenberg-block\">\n <div class=\"st-post-quote-container\">\n <div class=\"st-post-quote-content\">\n <div class=\"st-quote\">\n <div class=\"st-quote-fill\"><\/div>\n <div class=\"st-quote-body\">\n <div class=\"st-quote-grid\">\n <div class=\"st-quote-grid-col\">\n <div class=\"st-quote-icon\">\n <svg class=\"st-svgsprite -quote\">\n                                                <use\n xlink:href=\"\/assets\/img\/sprites\/svgsprites.svg#quote\"><\/use>\n                                            <\/svg>\n                                        <\/div>\n                                    <\/div>\n <div class=\"st-quote-grid-col\"><div class=\"st-quote-text\"><p>&#8216;Since you want to start your day at 7am, you may be tempted to set the alarm a bit early \u2013 let\u2019s say 6.40am \u2013and hit snooze a few times until it is 7am or maybe even 7.15am. But if you pick this snooze strategy, your body can\u2019t learn the conditioned response between hearing the alarm and getting up.&#8217; \u2013\u00a0Dan Ariely, Behavioural Scientist<\/p><\/div><div class=\"st-quote-author\"><\/div><div class=\"st-quote-social\">\n                                            <a class=\"st-quote-social-item\" href=\"http:\/\/twitter.com\/share?text='Since you want to start your day at 7am, you may be tempted to set the alarm a bit early \u2013 let\u2019s say 6.40am \u2013and hit snooze a few times until it is 7am or maybe even 7.15am. But if you pick this snooze strategy, your body can\u2019t learn the conditioned response between hearing the alarm and getting up.' \u2013\u00a0Dan Ariely, Behavioural Scientist&#038;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sleepiest.com%2Fblog%2Fwhy-hitting-snooze-could-be-bad-for-your-health%2F\" target=\"_blank\">Tweet<\/a>\n                                            <a class=\"st-quote-social-item\" href=\"https:\/\/www.facebook.com\/sharer\/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sleepiest.com%2Fblog%2Fwhy-hitting-snooze-could-be-bad-for-your-health%2F&#038;display=page\" target=\"_blank\">Facebook<\/a>\n                                        <\/div>\n                                    <\/div>\n                                <\/div>\n                            <\/div>\n                        <\/div>\n                    <\/div>\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div><div class=\"st-post-container gutenberg-block\">\n\n<\/div><div class=\"st-post-container gutenberg-block\">\n<p>It is much better to teach your brain a clear rule, so as not to confuse it or get into bad habits that will impact your health in the long run.<\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"st-post-container gutenberg-block\">\n\n<\/div><div class=\"st-post-container gutenberg-block\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"682\" src=\"https:\/\/www.sleepiest.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/sleeping-beauty.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-859\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.sleepiest.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/sleeping-beauty.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/www.sleepiest.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/sleeping-beauty-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/www.sleepiest.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/sleeping-beauty-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n<\/div><div class=\"st-post-container gutenberg-block\">\n\n<\/div><div class=\"st-post-container gutenberg-block\">\n<p>If you wake up every morning feeling tired, then the problem could lie in the amount of hours of sleep you are getting each night. You may need to increase the number of hours you sleep to feel more rested when you wake up. Instead of going to sleep later and snoozing for longer in the mornings, try going to bed earlier and wake up straight away to see if your tiredness levels improve.<\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"st-post-container gutenberg-block\">\n\n<\/div><div class=\"st-post-container gutenberg-block\">\n<p>Playing around with your sleep patterns could be the way to find out what truly works for you. You&#8217;ll be waking up feeling &#8216;fresh as a daisy&#8217; before you know it.<\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"st-post-container gutenberg-block\">\n\n<\/div><div class=\"st-post-container gutenberg-block\">\n<p><strong>If you struggle to get to sleep on an evening, why not try listening to one of our sleep stories available in the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.sleepiest.com\/\">Sleepiest app<\/a>.<\/strong><\/p>\n<\/div>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>We&#8217;re all guilty of hitting &#8216;snooze&#8217; on our alarms each morning we wake up. While some people are great in the morning and can easily hop out of bed, ready to attack the day, the rest of us struggle to drag ourselves out from under our comfy duvets. We tell ourselves that &#8216;just a couple [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_mi_skip_tracking":false},"categories":[6],"tags":[8,9],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.sleepiest.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/856"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.sleepiest.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.sleepiest.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.sleepiest.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/2"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.sleepiest.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=856"}],"version-history":[{"count":2,"href":"https:\/\/www.sleepiest.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/856\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":861,"href":"https:\/\/www.sleepiest.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/856\/revisions\/861"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.sleepiest.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=856"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.sleepiest.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=856"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.sleepiest.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\